visa / travel agencies that can do this for you and it takes about a week or 5 working days. costs vary but surprisingly they seem more expensive in south bali than it is in more rural locations further away from the immigration passport office. in south bali expect to pay between rp 600,000 to 750,000 or even more. elsewhere it can be as low as rp 500,000 such as in amed. a good place to find cheaper visa agents is at scuba diving centres. they often have divers wishing to stay longer and therefore know where to get visa 